Package com.csse3200.game.progression

Class Profile

java.lang.Object
com.csse3200.game.progression.Profile
public class Profile extends Object
Represents a user profile in the game. Allows customization of player attributes and tracking of progress.

    • Profile

      public Profile()

    • Profile

      public Profile(net.dermetfan.utils.Pair<String,String> nameAndLevel, net.dermetfan.utils.Pair<Wallet,Inventory> walletAndInventory, net.dermetfan.utils.Pair<SkillSet,Statistics> skillsetAndStatistics, net.dermetfan.utils.Pair<Set<String>,Set<String>> nodes, net.dermetfan.utils.Pair<Boolean,Boolean> tutorialsPlayed, net.dermetfan.utils.Pair<Float,Float> worldMapCoords, net.dermetfan.utils.Pair<Integer,Arsenal> zoomAndArsenal)
      Initialise a profile with the provided values.

      Using pairs to avoid a constructor with too many parameters. This is an antipattern and I do not care. Why is this a thing that can't be turned off?!

      Parameters:
      nameAndLevel - Pair containing the profile name and current level.
      walletAndInventory - Pair containing the wallet and inventory.
      skillsetAndStatistics - Pair containing the skillset and statistics.
      nodes - Pair containing the unlocked nodes and completed levels.
      tutorialsPlayed - Pair containing whether the level and map tutorials have been played.
      worldMapCoords - Pair containing the world map X and Y coordinates.
      zoomAndArsenal - Pair containing the world map zoom index and arsenal.
